NAME

Rstats - R language build on Perl (EXPERIMENTAL)

INSTALLATION

curl -L cpanmin.us | perl - -n  git@github.com:yuki-kimoto/Rstats.git

Usage

  use Rstats;
  my $r = Rstats->new;
  
  # Vector
  my $v1 = $r->c([1, 2, 3]);
  my $v2 = $r->c([2, 3, 4]);
  my $v3 = $v1 + v2;
  print $v3;

See examples in t directory to know current inplemented features.

Corresponding to R

  # 1:24
  c('1:24')

  # c(1, 2, 3)
  c([1, 2, 3])

  # array(1:24, c(4, 3, 2))
  array('1:24', [4, 3, 2])
  
  # a1 + a2
  $a1 + $a2
  
  # a1 - a2
  a1 - a2
  
  # a1 * a2
  a1 * a2
  
  # a1 / a2
  a1 / a2
  
  # a1 ^ a2 (power)
  a1 ** a2
  
  # a1 %% a2 (reminder)
  a1 % a2
  
  # a1 %/% a2 (integer quotient)
  $r->tranc($a1 / $a2)

  # as.matrix(a1)
  $r->as_matrix($a1)
  
  # as.vector(a1)
  $r->as_vector($a1)
  
  # as.array(a1)
  $r->as_array($a1);

